=== 其它地区 ===
菲律宾大气地球物理和天文服务管理局曾针对鸣蝉发布警报，还有其它气象机构担心风暴会令季风性雨季的降水增强，但气旋并未对菲律宾构成任何破坏<ref name="Pogi" /><ref name="gp" />。

台风在台湾以东洋面行进期间产生强降雨，其中[[宜兰县|宜兰县]]的降雨量最高，达227.5毫米<ref name="gp" />。降水缓解当地旱情的同时，也令干燥的水库得到补充<ref>{{cite news | newspaper = China Post | date = 2003-09-11 | title = Typhoon Maemi brings heavy rains to the island | accessdate = 2013-10-27 | archivedate = 2016-03-04 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160304223917/http://www.chinapost.com.tw/news/2003/09/11/41164/Typhoon-Maemi.htm | url = http://www.chinapost.com.tw/news/2003/09/11/41164/Typhoon-Maemi.htm }}</ref>。

鸣蝉在朝鲜产生约186毫米降水，但受该国[[朝鲜民主主义人民共和国审查制度|新闻审查制度]]的影响，风暴的进一步影响无法确知<ref name="usa914">{{cite news | agency = [[美联社|Associated Press]] | date = 2003-09-14 | title = Typhoon Maemi toll rises in South Korea | newspaper = [[今日美国|USA Today]] | accessdate = 2016-03-17 | url = http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/weather/hurricane/2003-09-13-skorea-typhoon_x.htm | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150404115910/http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/weather/hurricane/2003-09-13-skorea-typhoon_x.htm | archivedate = 2015-04-04 | deadurl = no}}</ref>。

== 善后 ==
[[File:Typhoon_Maemi_on_Sea_of_Japan_20030913.jpg|thumb]]
风暴过后，[[大韩民国总统|韩国总统]][[卢武铉|卢武铉]]在视察釜山的受灾情况后宣布全国除[[首尔|首尔]]和[[仁川广域市|仁川]]外均为特别灾区<ref name="gc" /><ref name="ocha915">{{cite report | agency = United Nations Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs | title = Republic of Korea: Typhoon Maemi OCHA Situation Report No. 1 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160304062603/http://reliefweb.int/report/republic-korea/republic-korea-typhoon-maemi-ocha-situation-report-no-1 | accessdate = 2013-10-24 | publisher = ReliefWeb | date = 2003-09-15 | archivedate = 2016-03-04 | url = http://reliefweb.int/report/republic-korea/republic-korea-typhoon-maemi-ocha-situation-report-no-1}}</ref>。2003年9月，[[韩国政府|韩国政府]]通过追加预算法案<ref name="kis922">{{cite report | title = Rep. of Korea: Supplemental budget set for typhoon victims | agency = Korean Information Service | date = 2003-09-22 | accessdate = 2016-03-17 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160304061504/http://reliefweb.int/report/republic-korea/rep-korea-supplemental-budget-set-typhoon-victims | url = http://reliefweb.int/report/republic-korea/rep-korea-supplemental-budget-set-typhoon-victims | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2016-03-04}}</ref>，并向灾民提供[[税收减免|税收减免]]，还拨出14000亿韩圆的援助金<ref name="gc" />。这其中包括立即生效的1000亿韩圆[[搜索及拯救|搜救任务]]资金{{refn||group="注"|name="won"}}<ref name="kis" />。气旋过去后，许多居民批评政府及气象机构没有及时发布足够警告，沿海地区疏散力度也有不足，导致大量人员遇难<ref>{{cite news | agency = United Press International | author = Jong-Heon Lee | date = 2003-09-15 | title = Analysis: Typhoon erodes Roh's popularity}}{{subscription required | via = Lexis Nexis}}</ref>。大范围的破坏和持续性的洪灾共同影响，导致交通状况在鸣蝉过去多天后依然得不到改善<ref name="usa914" />。受铁道损毁影响，铁道公司不得不暂时用客车来服务旅客。韩国各地发生多起山体滑坡，游客被迫另觅通途。<ref name="kh914" />台风过去3天后，大部分受损道路或高速公路已恢复通车<ref>{{cite news | agency = [[新华社|Xinhua News Agency]] | date = 2003-09-15 | url = http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2003-09/15/content_1082323.htm | title = Typhoon causes 1.3 billion USD in damage in S.Korea | accessdate = 2016-03-17 | archivedate = 2008-05-09 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080509130030/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2003-09/15/content_1082323.htm | deadurl = no}}{{subscription required | via = Lexis Nexis}}</ref>。政府派出约3万3000名[[大韩民国陆军|大韩民国陆军]]军人协助救灾<ref>{{cite news | agency = Xinhua News Agency | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080512022547/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2003-09/16/content_1084569.htm | deadurl = no | date = 2003-09-16 | url = http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2003-09/16/content_1084569.htm | title = S.Korea considering designate special disaster areas | accessdate = 2016-03-17 | archivedate = 2008-05-12}}{{subscription required | via = Lexis Nexis}}</ref>，执行清理道路、向灾民提供救灾物品等工作。工作人员在24小时内就恢复了95%断电用户的供电。<ref name="kis" />政府在釜山港新装4台起重机，协助工作人员确保商品出口不会延误<ref>{{cite news | newspaper = Korea Herald | author = Kim Hyun-chul | date = 2003-09-22 | title = Ministry to seek extra budget; Increased spending aims to repair W4.8 tril. typhoon damage}}{{subscription required | via = Lexis Nexis}}</ref>。沉重的农业损失致使水果和蔬菜价格上涨<ref name="jd916">{{cite news | author = Lee Sang-il | newspaper = JoongAng Daily | date = 2003-09-16 | title = Rep. of Korea: Was typhoon response slow? | publisher = ReliefWeb | accessdate = 2016-03-17 | url = http://reliefweb.int/report/republic-korea/rep-korea-was-typhoon-response-slow | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150402113050/http://reliefweb.int/report/republic-korea/rep-korea-was-typhoon-response-slow | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2015-04-02}}</ref>，鱼类和农产品出口价格平均涨幅达9.2%<ref>{{cite news | newspaper = Korea Herald | date = 2003-10-15 | title = Export, import prices dropped last month}}{{subscription required | via = Lexis Nexis}}</ref>。受风暴及此前政府限制生产的共同影响，韩国水稻收成创下23年来新低<ref>{{cite news | newspaper = Korea Times | date = 2003-11-15 | title = Rice Output Lowest in 23 Yrs}}{{subscription required | via = Lexis Nexis}}</ref>。政府为救助农民而加大农产品购买量，三家由政府运作的银行向风暴期间受灾的企业提供低息贷款<ref name="kis922" />。受积水经久不散的影响，韩国南部爆发[[结膜炎|结膜炎]]疫情<ref name="jd919" />。为防止更大范围传染，韩国国家卫生研究所派出上千名工作人员前往灾区控制疫情<ref>{{cite news | agency = Xinhua News Agency | author = Wang Mian | url = http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2003-09/14/content_1080670.htm | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2010-01-09 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20100109102603/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2003-09/14/content_1080670.htm | title = S. Korean govt tries to help victims of typhoon | accessdate = 2016-03-17 | date = 2003-09-14}}{{subscription required | via = Lexis Nexis}}</ref>。出于对风暴破坏影响出口的担忧，[[韩国交易所|韩国证券交易所]]跌幅达1.8%<ref>{{cite news | agency = Associated Press International | date = 2003-09-15 | title = Asian stock markets close generally mixed}}{{subscription required | via = Lexis Nexis}}</ref>。

[[韩国电力公社|韩国电力公社]]决定对那些失去家园的居民免收2003年9月电费，还把失去供电的居民和企业电费减半<ref>{{cite news | newspaper = Korea Times | date = 2003-09-16 | title = Typhoon Victims Waived on Electricity Charges}}{{subscription required | via = Lexis Nexis}}</ref>。面对大范围地区汽车损毁的情况，韩国政府同意保险公司提高汽车保险费用<ref name="gc" />。此外，有34家公司因风暴临时关闭<ref>{{cite news | newspaper = Korea Times | date = 2003-09-15 | title = W1.4 Tril. Earmarked for Storm Relief}}{{subscription required | via = Lexis Nexis}}</ref>，由此导致的减产和混乱估计使韩国2003年的[[经济增长|经济增长率]]减少了0.5个百分点<ref name="gc" />。韩国[[消费者信心指数|消费者信心指数]]降至5年间的新低，这场台风造成的破坏及对国家经济的不利影响正是这种情况的主要原因<ref>{{cite news | author = Koh Byung-joon | newspaper = Korea Herald | date = 2003-10-15 | title = Consumer sentiment hit record low in Sept.}}{{subscription required | via = Lexis Nexis}}</ref>。面对两年间台风鹿莎和鸣蝉先后来袭的情况，韩国政府开始着手制定灾害管理和减灾方案<ref name="dpri" />。在风暴同[[2003年大邱地铁纵火案|2003年大邱地铁纵火案]]的共同影响下，政府于2004年3月通过《应急和安全管理基本法》，行之有效地建立起全国性的应急管理体系<ref>{{cite report|author=Kyoo-Man Ha |title=Emergency Management in Korea: Just Started, but Rapidly Evolving |publisher=Federal Emergency Management Agency |accessdate=2013-10-29 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029200517/http://www.training.fema.gov/EMIWeb/edu/Comparative%20EM%20Book%20-%20Chapter%20-%20EM%20in%20Korea-Just%20Started%2C%20Rapidly%20EvolvingKorea1%20EM.doc |url=http://www.training.fema.gov/EMIWeb/edu/Comparative%20EM%20Book%20-%20Chapter%20-%20EM%20in%20Korea-Just%20Started,%20Rapidly%20EvolvingKorea1%20EM.doc |format=DOC |archivedate=2013-10-29 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。风暴期间受损的龟浦大桥直到2007年才修复<ref>{{cite journal | author1 = S.K. Park | author2 = P.Y. Julien | title = Case Study: Retrofitting Large Bridge Piers on the Nakdong River, South Korea | journal = Journal of Hydraulic Engineering | date = 2008-11 | volume = 134 | publisher = American Society of Civil Engineers | accessdate = 2015-02-18 | url = http://cedb.asce.org/cgi/WWWdisplay.cgi?167962 | doi = 10.1061/(ASCE)0733-9429(2008)134:11(1639) | issue = 8 | first3 = U. | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150218210036/http://cedb.asce.org/cgi/WWWdisplay.cgi?167962 | last3 = Ji | first4 = J. F. | last4 = Ruff | pages = 1639 | archivedate = 2015-02-18 | deadurl = yes}}</ref>。

虽然韩国政府并未请求国际社会援助，但还是有多个国家主动伸出援手<ref name="ocha915" />。台风过去数天后，[[美国国际开发署|美国国际开发署]]向韩国红十字会赠送5万美元<ref>{{cite report | agency = United States Department of State | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160304001505/http://reliefweb.int/report/republic-korea/us-gives-korean-red-cross-50000-disaster-relief | date = 2003-09-15 | title = U.S. gives Korean Red Cross $50,000 for disaster relief | publisher = ReliefWeb | url = http://reliefweb.int/report/republic-korea/us-gives-korean-red-cross-50000-disaster-relief | accessdate = 2016-03-17 | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2016-03-04}}</ref>。此后，[[日本政府|日本政府]]也向韩国赠送价格950万日圆（2003年日圆，相当于同年的8万5000美元{{refn||group="注"|name="jpy"}}）的救灾物资，其中包括睡垫、发电机和盛水容器<ref>{{cite report | agency = Government of Japan | date = 2003-09-17 | title = Emergency aid for typhoon disaster in the Republic of Korea | publisher = ReliefWeb | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160304064932/http://reliefweb.int/report/republic-korea/emergency-aid-typhoon-disaster-republic-korea | url = http://reliefweb.int/report/republic-korea/emergency-aid-typhoon-disaster-republic-korea | deadurl = no | accessdate = 2016-03-17 | archivedate = 2016-03-04}}</ref>。台湾也提供了10万美元的援助金<ref>{{cite report | agency = [[联合国人道事务协调厅|United Nations Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs]] | date = 2003-09-22 | title = Republic of Korea: Typhoon Maemi OCHA Situation Report No. 2 | publisher = ReliefWeb | accessdate = 2016-03-17 | url = http://reliefweb.int/report/republic-korea/republic-korea-typhoon-maemi-ocha-situation-report-no-2 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160304061005/http://reliefweb.int/report/republic-korea/republic-korea-typhoon-maemi-ocha-situation-report-no-2 | archivedate = 2016-03-04 | deadurl = no}}</ref>。[[韩国红十字会|韩国红十字会]]通过700名志愿者和200名工作人员，向8190户居民分发食品和毛毯，地方官员则提供了5500余顿膳食<ref name="ifrc915" />。[[粮食救济饥民国际协会|粮食救济饥民国际协会]]的工作人员在马山市向风暴灾民送去食品和衣物<ref>{{cite report | agency = Food for the Hungry | date = 2003-09-19 | title = Korea FHI aids Typhoon Maemi victims | publisher = ReliefWeb | accessdate = 2016-03-17 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160304042327/http://reliefweb.int/report/republic-korea/korea-fhi-aids-typhoon-maemi-victims | url = http://reliefweb.int/report/republic-korea/korea-fhi-aids-typhoon-maemi-victims | archivedate = 2016-03-04}}</ref>。

由于这场风暴造成大量人员伤亡和重大财产损失，[[世界气象组织|世界气象组织]]于2006年将其名称“鸣蝉”退役，以[[颱風彩虹|彩虹]]（{{lang|en|Mujigae}}）取代<ref>{{cite report | page = 31 | publisher = [[世界气象组织|World Meteorological Organization]] | title = Appendix 1C: List of Names for Tropical Cyclones Adopted by the Typhoon Committee for the Western North Pacific Ocean and the South China Sea | type = Typhoon Committee Operational Manual 2012 Edition | accessdate = 2016-03-17 | url = http://www.wmo.int/pages/prog/www/tcp/documents/TCP-23EDITION2012.pdf | format = PDF | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160303212136/http://www.wmo.int/pages/prog/www/tcp/documents/TCP-23EDITION2012.pdf | archivedate = 2016-03-03 | author = The Typhoon Committee}}</ref>。

